data.content:
Both are **C# 15 breaking changes**:

---

**1. `&&` with `dynamic` operand (DynamicOps.cs)**

`&&` is syntactic sugar: `T.false(left) ? left : T.&(left, right)`. It needs compile-time resolution of `operator true`/`false` and `operator &`. C# 15 now correctly errors here because the `dynamic` right operand forces runtime binding, which is incompatible with the compile-time short-circuit logic.

**Fix** — avoid mixing user-defined truth operators with `dynamic`:
```csharp
// Option A: use non-short-circuit &
var combined = left & right;

// Option B: cast away dynamic
var combined = left && (IFilter)right;
```

---

**2. `ref readonly` lambda (RefHelper.cs) — CS0518**

C# 15 now correctly emits `RequiresLocationAttribute` on `ref readonly` returns in lambdas (previously it was silently omitted). If `System.Runtime.CompilerServices.RequiresLocationAttribute` isn't available in your referenced assemblies, you get CS0518.

**Fix** — ensure your target framework provides the attribute. If you're multi-targeting or using an older BCL:
```csharp
// Option A: target net11.0 (attribute is included)

// Option B: if stuck on older BCL, define it yourself:
namespace System.Runtime.CompilerServices
{
    [AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Parameter | AttributeTargets.ReturnValue)]
    sealed class RequiresLocationAttribute : Attribute { }
}
```
